author: jgordon
title: Gabriel Jesus WON’T be able to keep up superstar performances, warns Manchester City team-mate Fernandinho
text:
3 Gabriel Jesus has sparked life into Manchester City since finally completing his switch last month 
But Fernandinho knows that his international colleague, 19, will suffer the same loss of form as other young players – although he can go for a while yet.

He said: “He has been a professional footballer for just two years, so he is starting very, very, very young. 
“We were happy for his incredible performances for the national team and for his club, where he won a few titles, and now he has come here and started to score goals. “I hope he can keep that level at least until the end of the season. 
“As a young player you can sometimes drop your level. He can play amazing, but he is good because his mentality is good, on the same level all the time – he is stable. "We can help him stay at this level until the end of the season, and if he does everyone will be happy. 
"If he scores more goals for us, I'll be the first to be happy." Manchester City 2 Swansea 1: Gabriel Jesus nets last-gasp winner
